The article discusses the 40th anniversary of Title IX, a law that requires equal access to academic and athletic opportunities for all students, regardless of gender. The article highlights the impact of Title IX, including the increase in the number of female college and high school athletes, as well as the increase in female professors in science and mathematics. The Obama Administration has worked to advance Title IX compliance and ensure equal access to educational opportunities in STEM fields. The article also mentions the White House event celebrating Title IX, which includes panel discussions and announcements of initiatives to further promote gender equity. The Administration has also taken steps to address sexual harassment and violence through Title IX enforcement and guidance. The Department of Education's Office for Civil Rights has initiated investigations into possible Title IX violations in athletics programs and obtained resolution agreements to ensure equal opportunities for female students.